@UriBram @florencehinder Linus (who's patched the same codebase for 3 decades) says that to fix a bug, you have to characterize the problem and invent a solution. 

These are often done by different people, and he thinks the first step is the harder one.

Cathedral and the Bazaar, if you want the quote.

@quinnnorton Right, agreed. 

But neither the old label nor the new ones cleave nature at the joints; bisexuality is no more or less real than pansexuality. 

Even queer, which comes closest, is still identitarian and oppositional in ways that I think are fading among cosmopolitan kids.

@BrianDeMare Co-sign @LetaHong 

Factory Girls, by Leslie Chang - not mainly a work of theory but very interesting on migrant women's lives in the factories of Shenzhen and Guangzhou
Social Media in Industrial China by Wang Xinyaun has interesting field work on similar issues

@waxpancake I wouldn't have needed to quit, because I would have been fired faster than I could have composed the "I resign for the Ctrl-V lulz" letter.

